ionContextRunner, which is provided by spring-boot-test and gives meaningful lightweight coverage without launching a full application.\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"agent_guidance\": \"Use the default in-memory Quartz JobStore; no Docker service is needed. Prefer a small ApplicationContextRunner test that registers a simple JobDetail/Trigger or verifies SchedulerFactoryBean/Scheduler creation, and ensure the Spring context or scheduler is closed after each run. Avoid switching to spring.quartz.job-store-type=jdbc unless the test also supplies an embedded DataSource and schema initialization.\",\n      \"risks\": [\n        \"The artifact also contains optional actuator endpoint classes; endpoint-specific coverage may require spring-boot-actuator, but core Quartz scheduler auto-configuration coverage does not.\",\n        \"Quartz starts scheduler threads when auto-startup is enabled, so tests must close the context or scheduler to avoid hangs.\"\n      ],\n      \"applied_setup\": [\n        {\n          \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n          \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-autoconfigure:4.1.0-RC1\",\n          \"result\": \"applied\",\n          \"target\": \"tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-quartz/4.1.0-RC1/build.gradle\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n          \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-test:4.1.0-RC1\",\n          \"result\": \"applied\",\n          \"target\": \"tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-quartz/4.1.0-RC1/build.gradle\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"input_evidence\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"issue\",\n          \"summary\": \"#8723 Support for org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-quartz:4.1.0-RC1; label=library-new-request; body_chars=39\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"existing_tests\",\n          \"summary\": \"0 existing test file path(s) included\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\",\n      \"inpu