ting build.gradle requirements**\\\\n\\\\nI’m facing a situation where the jar contains the endpoint but the POM lacks an actuator. I'm trying to understand how the classes compile in this scenario. It’s concerning that existing builds might rely on dependency resolution from autoconfiguration. The build.gradle file includes spring-boot-autoconfigure and boot-test, but not actuator, yet classes seem to compile. If I need to import the QuartzEndpoint, it may require the actuator classes. The task specifies modifying only the test file, but if it’s necessary, I might need to update build.gradle too.\\\\n\\\\n**Considering actuator imports and compilation**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about how using \\\\\\\"only test file\\\\\\\" as an exception might contradict the requirement. Should I use the provided library version for the spring boot actuator? I could bypass actuator imports by passing Collections.emptyList() and avoiding test sanitization. But then I wonder if the generic signature for the QuartzEndpoint might still need SanitizingFunction. As it stands, I think I can instantiate it without the actuator at compile time, which might be manageable. Yet, I'm unsure if Java requires the class for the constructor generic signature; it seems like javac could compile it as long as it doesn’t encounter missing classes during the signature check.\\\\n\\\\n**Analyzing class dependencies**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering whether the absence of the SanitizingFunction means we might avoid some issues, but I think nested classes implementing OperationResponseBody might still require their class files. If we're accessing methods from those nested classes, javac could indeed need the OperationResponseBody to compile successfully. As a workaround, I could add the actuator dependency or explore a different feature, like QuartzJdbcProperties, which extends DatabaseInitializationProperties from spring-boot-jdbc. I’m unsure if that dependency is transitive, but it seems like spring-boot-autoconfigure might cover it.\\\", \\\"thinkingSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"rs_085067120dea2f11016a3fe82c50c8819693c220358c8344bc\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"reasoning\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\":[],\\\\\\\"encrypted_content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"gAAAAABqP-g30zrGMYulTySlTj--gnZ3WKKSyck3e_mtjTRJhpHwx3MTrQsLE_15ieEHNlpCXP2Zxwb5SY6rOZATsX7XubnCW3IiKTl5m1dgIcPRNRFLJ_EQmeZ0HQlAkjvgz85MRhx6gYonPqYLFBdeivGIQ7cN8xrXVSfAMXiqJ5at5WOnfnS624rWjNUgbI_1gtUmzJSdFe2USIYgWM1YENRx86PFTqoqHRbLVjvsq2_kM8LmhcWSSXhpWC-x2rjUgoBRHQXOocxhSEEkO0JS4IqAxFtE1OHsfSm21SuIHppgNLFvchPuMcjOWEQFBng0I0NHrrvbN2tkhBogL1Ril3VvOXekLRXvu-OJ_Xq55CP22kUAGsN8Tq0O6bKqiKqUulD4Ify3vT5FIQ_h3XiyOZNZowQwL2CZ1TAje5fNPN2rDze0iuVmx56hhHbLoM0V040LrgmXobsNIGsAEcLc0UG8QmB2G7amrNv0wFjA-xFzwHHeOmtIQvxisWQax3qyF6SfTDCQNvY-mg_giTn3dGpy6_eDg7JFLHxIhme312HscNiY3WxAuvw6IaJIYxTPtPe7rsWL4CROFCsaL-_cBvXU8nXjf1oYF0c_PjRAWwzr8XYqKRxvOAQGuIn7_2cftGVlv6wZnw2nZnf1bbe-zpoyYnQmWvpmmixSsmGQ2X0R93oYHnqZrGo9gZCJo0ldsZuRxj7Rs-PbUP4RWOvfROPZNlp3E1aK96FOjneLlVTWUfAEKPHRvmyyuMxIVuZ0prrzJ026YgETu92KsocbegAvGY9DW1-vXs9hDZMufgLJ1GCyeiYOFgH6wmHl36HGeMWog9j9yysy5DoUM7FySGOmNR42hriZpdUUU0LTtc2ZKyJf8RQf5MRHerARt2psLBeNyCcfXRfbvl4jx0lCzbnXelHoqBgZ0y2CxtHR9s0VZAViW7pQEEjjKvOUAplwm5Z2YYYFXLWBYWd5ou3HbLgQ65sC-qhcf6G55NNXIXOixosg9f-9bJ0gDpVGtuI_SwG6IBNghjMLgjYF9N-WYc1O6vD0yF6SOPLbX3vOh3qcQWiiFm2HN-yIxMaNd5a3z-Z1-ZxJXEFgBtSBwHyXD4he9rU2KDGpgjBnq9sG3Gx4od7MqQKrhpWVCqshM2_ricitZ30zgXL3U_et2CRHnfJsAw_z3EcqaQoM3QDIa4EilK33B0vR71E73BLmokxvptMzhZcRkDZJe9Qnh15ytzJlq2E28-RzVSuQLZjYG5jHB1DhGxwVIofThqaKG2zDqaeYwDwJpMPPmqQ1eBaBYkSoOtwt_XZwjLDAJe7azWpJNas5sJdAJcen3Mnh_Jm8ESu4F1F32RmNiH79OE4xMiCgde8V-EzFixOfZg-t3YM8KNFwyCa1dd8N1ntfFKqpaMTyYgnTPTiPmbYcSPE8ptpyAMdpce4VtQb2h9ZM6THB78fVw71QoGBZNfI3nOBKsAJvETRK8WDI_Q2NQ8uZFHUY-rSPT584kjr_pe17-WHEtL-BVkUEFftPaHA7mlJh6ZNb3l6I1_jwtCnk8WU56Gq78coq83ASFPistz63rJl5qaN5BEzhP3rLBizyzFxhwvfigqb6RHNzx0XqGHFEe7gZg8_vQRgdv5Yk5FeIgPtDVUVvEUwMkDSJRNsGoS6eEURdemMCUHaaVJuYy2hsuXvCNtULS9c722mMg49uj_McjMQ0pJwC451nXycNDwUU0M2