,\\\\\\\"summary\\\\\\\":[{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"summary_text\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"**Evaluating scheduling and testing**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI’m considering that every test requires a connection timeout of at least 10 seconds. If I’m using CountDownLatch.await, I should also set that to 10 seconds. I need to close the scheduler; the context closes once it’s done running, and I might need to call scheduler.shutdown(true). \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBut would this not re-test registration? It seems to only test execution and the job factory. I’m wondering if the existing one auto-starts while the new one explicitly needs to start true with a Trigger set to start now. A job class with a default constructor may be required, and I should avoid direct reflection.\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"summary_text\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"**Evaluating testing concerns**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI'm focusing on testing the actual scheduling and SpringBeanJobFactory. There might be some flakiness, especially with a 10-second timeout. It's important to set each timeout to at least that. There's a potential issue with runtime reflective instantiation of a nested test job class, since metadata collection can complicate native tests. I need to ensure no dynamic class loading occurs outside the image. I'll be careful about editing imports and constants while adding the necessary components like CountDownLatch and AtomicReference for the new test.\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"summary_text\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"**Deciding on modifications**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI’m contemplating whether I need to modify the SampleQuartzJob’s execute function, especially if the executing job class is separate. It seems like it might be a good idea not to change anything there to keep things straightforward. I’ll proceed with the editing based on this understanding. It’s always nice to simplify where I can, and avoiding unnecessary changes could save time and potential complications. Let’s dive into the edits!\\\\\\\"}]}\\\"}, {\\\"type\\\": \\\"toolCall\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"call_IWLVPbZvBNkuUHyeGJAWm9sG|fc_085067120dea2f11016a3fe85b0d4081969ea4095bd3fdb41e\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"edit\\\", \\\"arguments\\\": {\\\"path\\\": \\\"tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-quartz/4.1.0-RC1/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot_quartz/Spring_boot_quartzTest.java\\\", \\\"edits\\\": [{\\\"oldText\\\": \\\"import java.util.Date;\\\\nimport java.util.List;\\\\nimport java.util.Map;\\\\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicBoolean;\\\\n\\\", \\\"newText\\\": \\\"import java.util.Date;\\\\nimport java.util.concurrent.CountDownLatch;\\\\nimport java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;\\\\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicBoolean;\\\\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicReference;\\\\n\\\"}, {\\\"oldText\\\": \\\"import org.springframework.beans.factory.BeanFactory;\\\\nimport org.springframework.boot.actuate.endpoint.SanitizableData;\\\\nimport org.springframework.boot.actuate.endpoint.SanitizingFunction;\\\\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.AutoConfigurations;\\\\nimport org.springframework.boot.quartz.actuate.endpoint.QuartzEndpoint;\\\\nimport org.springframework.boot.quartz.actuate.endpoint.QuartzEndpoint.QuartzDescriptor;\\\\nimport org.springframework.boot.quartz.actuate.endpoint.QuartzEndpoint.QuartzGroupsDescriptor;\\\\nimport org.springframework.boot.quartz.actuate.endpoint.QuartzEndpoint.QuartzJobDetailsDescriptor;\\\\nimport org.springframework.boot.quartz.actuate.endpoint.QuartzEndpoint.QuartzJobGroupSummaryDescriptor;\\\\nimport org.springframework.boot.quartz.actuate.endpoint.QuartzEndpoint.QuartzTriggerGroupSummaryDescriptor;\\\\n\\\", \\\"newText\\\": \\\"import org.springframework.beans.factory.BeanFactory;\\\\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.AutoConfigurations;\\\\n\\\"}, {\\\"oldText\\\": \\\"    private static final JobKey ENDPOINT_JOB_KEY = JobKey.jobKey(\\\\\\\"en